    <note>Peng(1) Siyong [1401] He was buried in Hezhou, Liyang county. His sons have the same generational name as Peng He's [1399] father, Kan [13113], and the two lineages may very well be branches of a common root lineage deriving from migrants to Jinling and then to other Jiangxi counties (e.g. Peng(1) Ruli [1400] and the Raozhou Peng). Han(1) Wei, WJ, 29.30b has his zi as Jichang with the wrong character for 'chang', but the correct title as Cheng(1) Hao's [3102] father-in-law. Cheng Yi, WJ, 7.1a records him as Hao's father-in-law with the correct zi. I suspect that his son-in-law, Qi(2) Yu (not in dataset) was a son of Qi(2) Hui [15751]. Cheng Hao, WJ, 3.3a-6b; Jiangxi TZ, 21.11b; Shen Gou, WJ, 2.12a; SS, 320.15a-16a; YLDD, 12429.15a-15b. CBD, 4, 2955.</note>
